ku: paint on window

build
 $sh mk get    #fenster.h from zserge
 $sh mk k.h    #build k.h, requires k
 $sh mk        #compiles ku.c
 $./a.out

k interface:   W:H:(size)  K:{[key]}  (paint):P[color;indexlist]

$ku x.k

W:H:200          /window size
B:P 255          /blue
G:P 255*256      /green
R:P 255*256*256  /red

K:{P[10*x;!W*H]} /key callback
